text: Antipolo, officially known as the City of Antipolo (), is a city and capital of the province of Rizal, Philippines. As of the 2020 census, 887,399 people lived there. It is the most populous city in the Calabarzon region and the seventh most-populous city in the Philippines. == References == Category:Cities in the Philippines Category:Provincial capitals of the Philippines Category:Settlements in Rizal
title: Antipolo
